    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'WASD to move, mouse to look

    You can "unlock" your mouse by holding
    right click, or left-Alt button

    Interact with the camera (the grey box the
    player starts looking at) with "e"

    You can swap cameras with A/D to go to
    the next or previous cameras - if you go past the "first" or "last" camera, it''ll
    kick you out of the camera view

    The two main rooms have anomalies that sometimes
    spawn, these are "differences" in the world that happen over time

    When you
    see something that is possibly an anomaly, you''ll need to first select the type
    of anomaly you think it is (by freeing your mouse and selecting from the dropdown
    on the left)

    Once you''ve chosen which anomaly type you think it is, you
    left click on the spot where the anomaly is happening

    After a brief delay
    it''ll tell you whether you were right or wrong, and if you were right it''ll
    fix it for you (though if another one spawns at the same time it might re-spawn
    the one you just fixed, this will be less of an issue in the future)

    If
    it doesn''t work but you think it should''ve, you either missed the anomaly with
    your click, or you chose the wrong anomaly type and should try a different type.

    Toggle
    Flashlight with "F". '
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
